      {
        "name": "Dance",
        "type": "skill",
        "img": "systems/projectfu/styles/static/compendium/classes/dancer/dancer_dance.png",
        "system": {
          "summary": {
            "value": ""
          },
          "description": "<p>Each time you take this Skill, you learn a <strong>dance</strong>.</p><p>On your turn during a conflict scene, if you have <strong>no martial armor</strong> equipped, you may spend 10 Mind Points to <strong>perform a dance</strong> you have learned. This doesn’t require an action, but it can only be done <strong>once per turn</strong>, while no other effect is being resolved. If you already performed a <strong>different dance</strong> during your previous turn in this scene, the cost of the new <strong>dance</strong> is reduced to 5 Mind Points.</p><p>Some <strong>dances</strong> are <strong>instantaneous</strong> and resolve immediately, while others have effects that last <strong>until the start of your next turn</strong>.</p><hr /><p>For <strong>dance</strong> breakdown and a list of <strong>Dances</strong>, refer to: @UUID[Compendium.projectfu.handouts.JournalEntry.cH2N0pg4NeNZpaM5]{Dancer Rules} or see <strong>High Fantasy</strong>, page <strong>144</strong>.<br /><strong>You Spend (reduced)</strong>: @LOSS[5 mp]</p>",
          "showTitleCard": {
            "value": false
          },
          "level": {
            "value": 0,
            "max": 10,
            "min": 0
          },
